      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SETTLE THE BILL (1) ran fifth last start at Kilmore over 1690m, beaten 15 metres. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Taking on a better field but she is capable of running a big race. BISHOP GEORGE (8) has raced two times this prep and has filled a minor placing on each occasion. Went well again last time over 1800m at this track, finishing second and 3.5 metres from the winner. Can travel in a nice spot from this draw and wait on the sprint lane if necessary and rates a big chance based on what we have seen of late. DAISY BOUCHEA (3) was out of the money two runs ago then broke and finished seventh last start over 1800m here, coming home 24 metres from the winner. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Live chance in a similar assignment. THE VICARS GIRL (9) has been hard to fault of late, adding to the winning tally last start with success over 2050m at Port Pirie. Has to be included in calculations.",
